<p class="fd-paragraph">
  AI agents that actively manage queue load — triaging, reassigning, and completing tasks within queues without waiting for human direction. Queue depth shrinks automatically as agents work in parallel.
</p>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">What it does</h2>
<ul class="fd-list">
  <li class="fd-list-item">Agents triage incoming queue items by acuity, urgency, and patient risk</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Parallel agent execution reduces queue depth continuously throughout the day</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Automatic reassignment when staff capacity changes or items age out</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Supervisors see real-time queue health without manual monitoring</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">Why it matters</h2>
<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Queues grow faster than teams can work them. Agentic Queue Management inverts that dynamic — agents absorb volume so staff can focus on the cases that genuinely need human attention.
</p>
